      <div class="defi">
        <div class="type-heding">
          <h2>TYPE OF DONATION</h2>
        </div>
        <p>The human body typically contains around five liters of blood, a complex mixture of cellular and non-cellular
          elements like red <b>blood cells</b>, <b>platelets</b>, and <b>platelets</b>.

        </p>
        <p>
          Each component has distinct properties, making it valuable for various medical needs. At blood centers,
          donated
          blood is carefully divided into these components, allowing a single donation to potentially impact up to four
          lives, depending on the number of separate components that can be derived from it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="creteria">
        <div class="creteria-one">
          <div class="div-one">
            <h2>What is it?</h2>
            <p>
              Blood collected directly from a donor into a blood bag containing an anticoagulant is known as whole
              blood.
              This whole blood is then processed through centrifugation to separate it into red cells, platelets, and
              plasma. The separated red cells are then preserved with a special solution, transforming them into what is
              known as packed red blood cells.

            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="div-two">
            <h2>Who can donate?</h2>
            <p>
              You need to be 18-65 years old, weight 45kg or more and be fit and healthy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="creteria-two">
          <div class="div-one">
            <h2>User For?</h2>
            <p>
              Treatment for severe anemia in various conditions, as well as blood loss during childbirth, surgery, or
              trauma situations.

            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="div-two">
            <h2>Lasts For?</h2>
            <p>
              Red cells can be stored for 42 days at 2-6 degree celsius.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="creteria-three">
          <div class="div-one">
            <h2>How long does it take to donate?</h2>
            <p>
              The donation process, including the pre-donation check-up, takes approximately 15-30 minutes.

            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="div-two">
            <h2>How often can I donate?</h2>
            <p>
              Male donors are eligible to donate every 90 days, while female donors can donate every 120 days.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
