          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="bloodtype-para">
          <p>
            Blood types are classified by the <b>ABO system</b> and the <b>Rh factor</b>, based on antigens on red blood
            cells. In the ABO system: Type A has A antigens, Type B has B antigens, Type AB has both, and Type O has
            none.
            Additionally, Rh-positive blood has the Rh antigen, while Rh-negative does not. Compatibility is crucial for
            transfusions, with Type O as the universal donor and AB as the universal plasma donor.
          </p>
        </div>
