            <p>
              Compatible blood type donors are crucial for safe blood transfusions. Type O- is known as the universal
              donor for red blood cells, as it can be safely given to any blood type. Type AB+, on the other hand, is
              the
              universal recipient, able to receive red blood cells from any type. Compatibility depends on both the ABO
              and Rh systems: for example, Type A can receive from A and O, while Type B can receive from B and O.
              Matching donor and recipient blood types minimizes immune reactions, ensuring safe and effective
              transfusions.
            </p>
